vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-53838', 'GHSA-83W9-H5WV-J9XM']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-53836 - OpenClaw < 2026.5.12 - Allowlist Bypass via PowerShell Encoded-Command Aliases', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 12 Jun 2026 22:16:55 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-53836', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['OpenClaw before 2026.5.12 contains an allowlist bypass vulnerability in PowerShell encoded-command handling that allows attackers to execute encoded commands using abbreviated flag aliases not recognized by the allowlist parser. Remote authenticated operators can bypass execution allowlist checks by using unrecognized encoded-command alias forms to execute arbitrary PowerShell content.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-53836vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-53836weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-allowlist-bypass-via-powershell-encoded-command-aliases', 'https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/security/advisories/GHSA-j472-gf56-x589', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-allowlist-bypass-via-powershell-encoded-command-aliases'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-53836', 'GHSA-J472-GF56-X589']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-53834 - OpenClaw < 2026.4.27 - Authorization Bypass in QQBot Pre-dispatch Slash Commands', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 12 Jun 2026 22:16:55 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-53834', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['OpenClaw before 2026.4.27 contains an authorization bypass vulnerability in QQBot pre-dispatch slash commands that allows authenticated senders to skip allowFrom policy checks. Attackers can invoke slash commands before configured access control policies are applied, potentially triggering command handling from blocked senders depending on operator configuration.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-53834vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-53834weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-authorization-bypass-in-qqbot-pre-dispatch-slash-commands', 'https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/security/advisories/GHSA-77pv-3w4q-vrj5', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-authorization-bypass-in-qqbot-pre-dispatch-slash-commands'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-53834', 'GHSA-77PV-3W4Q-VRJ5']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-53831 - OpenClaw < 2026.5.18 - Arbitrary File Read via Shell Expansion in system.run Safe-bin Allowlist', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 12 Jun 2026 22:16:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-53831', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['OpenClaw before 2026.5.18 contains a policy enforcement vulnerability in system.run safe-bin allowlist validation that allows shell expansion to modify command interpretation on POSIX nodes. Authenticated operators can exploit shell metacharacters in approved commands to read unintended node-local files and expose sensitive configuration data.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-53831vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-53831weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-arbitrary-file-read-via-shell-expansion-in-system-run-safe-bin-allowlist', 'https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/security/advisories/GHSA-mhq8-78pj-5j79', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-arbitrary-file-read-via-shell-expansion-in-system-run-safe-bin-allowlist'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-53831', 'GHSA-MHQ8-78PJ-5J79']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-53829 - OpenClaw < 2026.5.18 - Command Truncation in Exec Approval Display', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 12 Jun 2026 22:16:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-53829', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['OpenClaw before 2026.5.18 contains an approval display truncation vulnerability allowing authenticated users to hide command suffixes from approvers. Attackers can submit oversized exec commands with benign prefixes and malicious suffixes to execute unauthorized operations after approval.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-53829vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-53829weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-command-truncation-in-exec-approval-display', 'https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/security/advisories/GHSA-xww8-gqvh-92x9', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-command-truncation-in-exec-approval-display'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-53829', 'GHSA-XWW8-GQVH-92X9']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-53828 - OpenClaw < 2026.5.6 - Native Command Authorization Bypass via Owner-Command Enforcement', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 12 Jun 2026 22:16:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-53828', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['OpenClaw before 2026.5.6 contains an authorization bypass vulnerability in native command handling that allows authenticated senders to execute owner-only commands without proper policy enforcement. Attackers can trigger native command handling to bypass the configured owner-command access control, potentially executing privileged commands from unauthorized users.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-53828vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-53828weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-native-command-authorization-bypass-via-owner-command-enforcement', 'https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/security/advisories/GHSA-p73f-w79w-jqr5', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-native-command-authorization-bypass-via-owner-command-enforcement'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-53828', 'GHSA-P73F-W79W-JQR5']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans Google Chrome (12 juin 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00: